Note:
Runa Standard Library: TAR Archive Module

Provides production-ready TAR (Tape Archive) format support for creating, extracting,
and manipulating archive files. Supports POSIX.1-1988 (ustar), POSIX.1-2001 (pax),
and GNU tar extensions with optional compression integration.

Features:
- Complete TAR format support (POSIX ustar, GNU tar, pax format)
- Integration with compression algorithms (gzip, bzip2, lzma, xz)
- Stream-based archive creation and extraction for large files
- Memory-efficient operations with configurable buffer sizes
- Comprehensive error handling with detailed diagnostics
- Progress tracking for long-running archive operations
- Thread-safe operations for concurrent archive processing
- Integration with Runa's advanced type system for type safety
- Advanced file metadata preservation (permissions, ownership, timestamps)
- Symbolic and hard link support with proper handling
- Extended attribute support for modern filesystems
- Directory traversal with filtering and exclusion patterns
- Archive verification and integrity checking
- Cross-platform compatibility with proper path handling

Technical specifications:
- Format support: POSIX ustar, GNU tar, pax (POSIX.1-2001)
- Compression integration: gzip (.tar.gz, .tgz), bzip2 (.tar.bz2), lzma (.tar.xz)
- Maximum file size: 8GB (ustar), unlimited (GNU/pax)
- Maximum path length: 255 chars (ustar), unlimited (GNU/pax)
- Thread safety: All operations are thread-safe and reentrant
- Memory usage: Configurable buffer sizes for memory efficiency
- Error recovery: Robust error handling with detailed diagnostics
:End Note

Import "compress/gzip" as gzip_module
Import "compress/bz2" as bz2_module
Import "compress/lzma" as lzma_module

Note: Core TAR Types and Configuration
Type called "TARConfig":
    format as String defaults to "ustar"
    compression as String defaults to "none"
    compression_level as Integer defaults to 6
    preserve_permissions as Boolean defaults to true
    preserve_ownership as Boolean defaults to false
    preserve_timestamps as Boolean defaults to true
    preserve_extended_attributes as Boolean defaults to false
    follow_symlinks as Boolean defaults to false
    create_directories as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_progress_tracking as Boolean defaults to false
    buffer_size as Integer defaults to 65536
    block_size as Integer defaults to 512
    record_size as Integer defaults to 10240
    enable_verification as Boolean defaults to true
    exclusion_patterns as List[String] defaults to list containing
    inclusion_patterns as List[String] defaults to list containing
    base_directory as Optional[String] defaults to None
    owner_override as Optional[String] defaults to None
    group_override as Optional[String] defaults to None
    mode_override as Optional[Integer] defaults to None
    enable_sparse_files as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_incremental as Boolean defaults to false
    snapshot_file as Optional[String] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type TARResult is:
    | TARSuccess with archive_path as String and operation as String and files_processed as Integer and total_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and processing_time as Float and format as String
    | TARError with error_message as String and error_code as String and archive_path as String and operation as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TARFileInfo":
    path as String
    name as String
    size as Integer
    mode as Integer
    uid as Integer
    gid as Integer
    mtime as Integer
    atime as Integer
    ctime as Integer
    file_type as String
    link_target as Optional[String]
    owner as String
    group as String
    device_major as Integer
    device_minor as Integer
    checksum as String
    extended_attributes as Dictionary[String, String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TARHeader":
    name as String
    mode as String
    uid as String
    gid as String
    size as String
    mtime as String
    checksum as String
    typeflag as String
    linkname as String
    magic as String
    version as String
    uname as String
    gname as String
    devmajor as String
    devminor as String
    prefix as String
    raw_data as List[Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type TARFormat is:
    | USTAR | GNU | PAX

Type TARCompression is:
    | None | GZIP | BZIP2 | LZMA | XZ

Type TARFileType is:
    | RegularFile | Directory | SymbolicLink | HardLink | CharacterDevice | BlockDevice | FIFO | ContiguousFile

Type called "TAREntry":
    header as TARHeader
    file_info as TARFileInfo
    data_offset as Integer
    data_size as Integer
    is_sparse as Boolean
    sparse_map as List[Dictionary[String, Integer]]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TARArchiveContext":
    config as TARConfig
    format as TARFormat
    compression as TARCompression
    file_count as Integer
    total_size as Integer
    current_offset as Integer
    entries as List[TAREntry]
    compression_stream as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    verification_data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
:End Note

Note: Core TAR Archive Functions
Process called "create_tar_archive" that takes files as List[String] and archive_path as String and config as Optional[TARConfig] returns TARResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_tar_config
    
    Try:
        If length of files is equal to 0:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create TAR archive with no files"
                error_code as "TAR_EMPTY_FILE_LIST"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "create"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide at least one file to archive"
                context as dictionary containing "file_count" as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_tar_config with config as final_config
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Invalid TAR configuration: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "TAR_INVALID_CONFIG"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "create"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing "config" as final_config
        
        Let missing_files be find_missing_files with files as files
        If length of missing_files is greater than 0:
            Let missing_list be join_list with list as missing_files and separator as ", "
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Files not found: " plus missing_list
                error_code as "TAR_FILES_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "create"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify all file paths are correct", "Check file permissions"
                context as dictionary containing "missing_files" as missing_files
        
        Let archive_context be initialize_tar_archive_context with config as final_config and archive_path as archive_path
        Let file_list be expand_file_list with files as files and config as final_config
        
        Let creation_result be create_tar_archive_with_context with:
            file_list as file_list
            archive_path as archive_path
            context as archive_context
        
        Match creation_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return TARSuccess with:
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "create"
                    files_processed as creation_result.files_processed
                    total_size as creation_result.total_size
                    compressed_size as creation_result.compressed_size
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    format as final_config.format
            
            When "error":
                Return TARError with:
                    error_message as creation_result.error_message
                    error_code as creation_result.error_code
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "create"
                    suggestions as creation_result.suggestions
                    context as creation_result.context
    
    Catch error:
        Return TARError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected TAR creation error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "TAR_CREATE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            archive_path as archive_path
            operation as "create"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify file permissions", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "extract_tar_archive" that takes archive_path as String and output_directory as String and config as Optional[TARConfig] returns TARResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_tar_config
    
    Try:
        Let archive_exists be check_file_exists with path as archive_path
        If not archive_exists:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "TAR archive does not exist: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "TAR_ARCHIVE_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "extract"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify archive path is correct", "Check file permissions"
                context as dictionary containing
        
        Let format_detection be detect_tar_format with path as archive_path
        If format_detection.format is equal to "unknown":
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Cannot determine TAR archive format: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "TAR_UNKNOWN_FORMAT"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "extract"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file is a valid TAR archive", "Check for file corruption"
                context as dictionary containing "detected_format" as format_detection.format
        
        Let dir_created be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_directory
        If not dir_created:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_directory
                error_code as "TAR_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "extract"
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
                context as dictionary containing "output_directory" as output_directory
        
        Let archive_context be initialize_tar_extraction_context with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            output_directory as output_directory
            config as final_config
            format as format_detection.format
            compression as format_detection.compression
        
        Let extraction_result be extract_tar_archive_with_context with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            output_directory as output_directory
            context as archive_context
        
        Match extraction_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return TARSuccess with:
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "extract"
                    files_processed as extraction_result.files_processed
                    total_size as extraction_result.total_size
                    compressed_size as extraction_result.compressed_size
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    format as format_detection.format
            
            When "error":
                Return TARError with:
                    error_message as extraction_result.error_message
                    error_code as extraction_result.error_code
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "extract"
                    suggestions as extraction_result.suggestions
                    context as extraction_result.context
    
    Catch error:
        Return TARError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected TAR extraction error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "TAR_EXTRACT_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            archive_path as archive_path
            operation as "extract"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify archive integrity", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "list_tar_contents" that takes archive_path as String and config as Optional[TARConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_tar_config
    
    Try:
        Let archive_exists be check_file_exists with path as archive_path
        If not archive_exists:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "TAR archive does not exist: " plus archive_path
                "error_code" as "TAR_ARCHIVE_NOT_FOUND"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Verify archive path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let format_detection be detect_tar_format with path as archive_path
        If format_detection.format is equal to "unknown":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot determine TAR archive format: " plus archive_path
                "error_code" as "TAR_UNKNOWN_FORMAT"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Verify file is a valid TAR archive", "Check for file corruption"
        
        Let listing_result be list_tar_entries with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            format as format_detection.format
            compression as format_detection.compression
            config as final_config
        
        If listing_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "entries" as listing_result.entries
                "total_files" as listing_result.total_files
                "total_size" as listing_result.total_size
                "archive_format" as format_detection.format
                "compression" as format_detection.compression
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as listing_result.error_message
                "error_code" as listing_result.error_code
                "suggestions" as listing_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Unexpected TAR listing error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "TAR_LIST_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            "suggestions" as list containing "Check archive integrity", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "add_to_tar_archive" that takes archive_path as String and files as List[String] and config as Optional[TARConfig] returns TARResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_tar_config
    
    Try:
        If length of files is equal to 0:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Cannot add empty file list to TAR archive"
                error_code as "TAR_EMPTY_ADD_LIST"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "add"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide at least one file to add"
                context as dictionary containing "file_count" as 0
        
        Let archive_exists be check_file_exists with path as archive_path
        If not archive_exists:
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "TAR archive does not exist: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "TAR_ARCHIVE_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "add"
                suggestions as list containing "Create archive first using create_tar_archive", "Verify archive path is correct"
                context as dictionary containing
        
        Let format_detection be detect_tar_format with path as archive_path
        If format_detection.compression is not equal to "none":
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Cannot add files to compressed TAR archive: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "TAR_COMPRESSED_ARCHIVE_READONLY"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "add"
                suggestions as list containing "Extract, modify, and recreate archive", "Use uncompressed TAR for incremental updates"
                context as dictionary containing "compression" as format_detection.compression
        
        Let missing_files be find_missing_files with files as files
        If length of missing_files is greater than 0:
            Let missing_list be join_list with list as missing_files and separator as ", "
            Return TARError with:
                error_message as "Files not found: " plus missing_list
                error_code as "TAR_FILES_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as archive_path
                operation as "add"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify all file paths are correct", "Check file permissions"
                context as dictionary containing "missing_files" as missing_files
        
        Let addition_result be add_files_to_tar_archive with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            files as files
            format as format_detection.format
            config as final_config
        
        Match addition_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return TARSuccess with:
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "add"
                    files_processed as addition_result.files_processed
                    total_size as addition_result.total_size
                    compressed_size as addition_result.compressed_size
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    format as format_detection.format
            
            When "error":
                Return TARError with:
                    error_message as addition_result.error_message
                    error_code as addition_result.error_code
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "add"
                    suggestions as addition_result.suggestions
                    context as addition_result.context
    
    Catch error:
        Return TARError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected TAR addition error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "TAR_ADD_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            archive_path as archive_path
            operation as "add"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify file permissions", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "verify_tar_archive" that takes archive_path as String and config as Optional[TARConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_tar_config
    
    Try:
        Let archive_exists be check_file_exists with path as archive_path
        If not archive_exists:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "TAR archive does not exist: " plus archive_path
                "error_code" as "TAR_ARCHIVE_NOT_FOUND"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Verify archive path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let format_detection be detect_tar_format with path as archive_path
        If format_detection.format is equal to "unknown":
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot determine TAR archive format: " plus archive_path
                "error_code" as "TAR_UNKNOWN_FORMAT"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Verify file is a valid TAR archive", "Check for file corruption"
        
        Let verification_result be verify_tar_archive_integrity with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            format as format_detection.format
            compression as format_detection.compression
            config as final_config
        
        If verification_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "is_valid" as verification_result.is_valid
                "total_files" as verification_result.total_files
                "total_size" as verification_result.total_size
                "checksum_errors" as verification_result.checksum_errors
                "format_errors" as verification_result.format_errors
                "warnings" as verification_result.warnings
                "archive_format" as format_detection.format
                "compression" as format_detection.compression
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as verification_result.error_message
                "error_code" as verification_result.error_code
                "suggestions" as verification_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Unexpected TAR verification error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "TAR_VERIFY_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            "suggestions" as list containing "Check archive integrity", "Report this as a bug"
:End Note

Note: TAR Header Processing Functions
Process called "create_tar_header" that takes file_info as TARFileInfo and format as String returns TARHeader:
    Let header be TARHeader with:
        name as truncate_path_for_format with path as file_info.path and format as format
        mode as format_octal_string with value as file_info.mode and width as 8
        uid as format_octal_string with value as file_info.uid and width as 8
        gid as format_octal_string with value as file_info.gid and width as 8
        size as format_octal_string with value as file_info.size and width as 12
        mtime as format_octal_string with value as file_info.mtime and width as 12
        checksum as ""
        typeflag as get_typeflag_for_file_type with file_type as file_info.file_type
        linkname as file_info.link_target if file_info.link_target is not None else ""
        magic as get_magic_for_format with format as format
        version as get_version_for_format with format as format
        uname as file_info.owner
        gname as file_info.group
        devmajor as format_octal_string with value as file_info.device_major and width as 8
        devminor as format_octal_string with value as file_info.device_minor and width as 8
        prefix as ""
        raw_data as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let checksum_value be calculate_tar_header_checksum with header as header
    Set header.checksum to format_octal_string with value as checksum_value and width as 8
    
    Return header

Process called "parse_tar_header" that takes data as List[Integer] and offset as Integer returns Optional[TARHeader]:
    Try:
        If length of data is less than (offset plus 512):
            Return None
        
        Let header_block be slice_byte_array with data as data and start as offset and end as (offset plus 512)
        
        Let header be TARHeader with:
            name as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 0 and length as 100
            mode as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 100 and length as 8
            uid as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 108 and length as 8
            gid as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 116 and length as 8
            size as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 124 and length as 12
            mtime as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 136 and length as 12
            checksum as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 148 and length as 8
            typeflag as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 156 and length as 1
            linkname as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 157 and length as 100
            magic as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 257 and length as 6
            version as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 263 and length as 2
            uname as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 265 and length as 32
            gname as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 297 and length as 32
            devmajor as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 329 and length as 8
            devminor as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 337 and length as 8
            prefix as extract_string_field with data as header_block and start as 345 and length as 155
            raw_data as header_block
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let calculated_checksum be calculate_tar_header_checksum with header as header
        Let stored_checksum be parse_octal_string with string as header.checksum
        
        If calculated_checksum is not equal to stored_checksum:
            Set header.metadata["checksum_invalid"] to true
        
        Return header
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "calculate_tar_header_checksum" that takes header as TARHeader returns Integer:
    Let header_bytes be serialize_tar_header_to_bytes with header as header
    Let checksum be 0
    
    For i from 0 to 511:
        If i is greater than or equal to 148 and i is less than 156:
            Set checksum to checksum plus 32  Note: Space character for checksum field
        Otherwise:
            Set checksum to checksum plus header_bytes[i]
    
    Return checksum

Process called "validate_tar_header" that takes header as TARHeader returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let errors be list containing
    
    If length of header.name is equal to 0:
        Add "Empty file name" to errors
    
    If header.magic is not equal to "ustar " and header.magic is not equal to "ustar\0":
        Add "Invalid magic number: " plus header.magic to errors
    
    Let size_value be parse_octal_string with string as header.size
    If size_value is less than 0:
        Add "Invalid file size: " plus header.size to errors
    
    Let valid_typeflags be list containing "0", "1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7", "g", "x", "A", "I", "K", "L", "M", "N", "S", "V", "X"
    If not valid_typeflags contains header.typeflag:
        Add "Invalid type flag: " plus header.typeflag to errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as length of errors is equal to 0
        "errors" as errors
        "warnings" as list containing
:End Note

Note: Compression Integration Functions
Process called "create_compressed_tar_stream" that takes compression as String and config as TARConfig returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Match compression:
        When "gzip":
            Let gzip_config be create_gzip_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return gzip_module.gzip_create_compression_stream with config as gzip_config
        
        When "bzip2":
            Let bz2_config be create_bz2_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return bz2_module.bz2_create_compression_stream with config as bz2_config
        
        When "lzma" or "xz":
            Let lzma_config be create_lzma_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return lzma_module.lzma_create_compression_stream with config as lzma_config
        
        Otherwise:
            Return None

Process called "create_decompression_stream" that takes compression as String and config as TARConfig returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Match compression:
        When "gzip":
            Let gzip_config be create_gzip_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return gzip_module.gzip_create_decompression_stream with config as gzip_config
        
        When "bzip2":
            Let bz2_config be create_bz2_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return bz2_module.bz2_create_decompression_stream with config as bz2_config
        
        When "lzma" or "xz":
            Let lzma_config be create_lzma_config_from_tar_config with config as config
            Return lzma_module.lzma_create_decompression_stream with config as lzma_config
        
        Otherwise:
            Return None

Process called "compress_tar_data" that takes compression_stream as Dictionary[String, Any] and data as List[Integer] and compression as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match compression:
        When "gzip":
            Let data_string be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as data
            Return gzip_module.gzip_compress_stream_data with stream_context as compression_stream and data as data_string
        
        When "bzip2":
            Let data_string be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as data
            Return bz2_module.bz2_compress_stream_data with stream_context as compression_stream and data as data_string
        
        When "lzma" or "xz":
            Let data_string be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as data
            Return lzma_module.lzma_compress_stream_data with stream_context as compression_stream and data as data_string
        
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "error_message" as "Unsupported compression format"

Process called "decompress_tar_data" that takes decompression_stream as Dictionary[String, Any] and data as List[Integer] and compression as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match compression:
        When "gzip":
            Return gzip_module.gzip_decompress_stream_data with stream_context as decompression_stream and compressed_data as data
        
        When "bzip2":
            Return bz2_module.bz2_decompress_stream_data with stream_context as decompression_stream and compressed_data as data
        
        When "lzma" or "xz":
            Return lzma_module.lzma_decompress_stream_data with stream_context as decompression_stream and compressed_data as data
        
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "error_message" as "Unsupported compression format"
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_tar_config" returns TARConfig:
    Return TARConfig with:
        format as "ustar"
        compression as "none"
        compression_level as 6
        preserve_permissions as true
        preserve_ownership as false
        preserve_timestamps as true
        preserve_extended_attributes as false
        follow_symlinks as false
        create_directories as true
        enable_progress_tracking as false
        buffer_size as 65536
        block_size as 512
        record_size as 10240
        enable_verification as true
        exclusion_patterns as list containing
        inclusion_patterns as list containing
        base_directory as None
        owner_override as None
        group_override as None
        mode_override as None
        enable_sparse_files as true
        enable_incremental as false
        snapshot_file as None
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "validate_tar_config" that takes config as TARConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let errors be list containing
    
    Let valid_formats be list containing "ustar", "gnu", "pax"
    If not valid_formats contains config.format:
        Add "Invalid TAR format: " plus config.format to errors
    
    Let valid_compressions be list containing "none", "gzip", "bzip2", "lzma", "xz"
    If not valid_compressions contains config.compression:
        Add "Invalid compression format: " plus config.compression to errors
    
    If config.compression_level is less than 0 or config.compression_level is greater than 9:
        Add "Compression level must be between 0 and 9" to errors
    
    If config.buffer_size is less than 512:
        Add "Buffer size must be at least 512 bytes" to errors
    
    If config.block_size is not equal to 512:
        Add "Block size must be 512 bytes for TAR compatibility" to errors
    
    If config.record_size modulo config.block_size is not equal to 0:
        Add "Record size must be a multiple of block size" to errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as length of errors is equal to 0
        "error_message" as join_list with list as errors and separator as "; "
        "suggestions" as list containing "Check TAR configuration parameters", "Use create_default_tar_config for valid defaults"

Process called "detect_tar_format" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let file_data be read_file_bytes with path as path and count as 2048
        If file_data is None or length of file_data is less than 512:
            Return dictionary containing "format" as "unknown", "compression" as "none"
        
        Let compression be detect_compression_format with data as file_data
        Let decompressed_data be file_data
        
        If compression is not equal to "none":
            Let decompression_result be decompress_header_data with data as file_data and compression as compression
            If decompression_result.success:
                Set decompressed_data to decompression_result.data
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing "format" as "unknown", "compression" as compression
        
        Let header be parse_tar_header with data as decompressed_data and offset as 0
        If header is None:
            Return dictionary containing "format" as "unknown", "compression" as compression
        
        Let format be determine_tar_format_from_header with header as header
        
        Return dictionary containing "format" as format, "compression" as compression
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing "format" as "unknown", "compression" as "none"

Process called "detect_compression_format" that takes data as List[Integer] returns String:
    If length of data is less than 4:
        Return "none"
    
    If data[0] is equal to 31 and data[1] is equal to 139:
        Return "gzip"
    
    If data[0] is equal to 66 and data[1] is equal to 90 and data[2] is equal to 104:
        Return "bzip2"
    
    If length of data is greater than 5 and data[0] is equal to 253 and data[1] is equal to 55 and data[2] is equal to 122 and data[3] is equal to 88 and data[4] is equal to 90 and data[5] is equal to 0:
        Return "xz"
    
    If length of data is greater than 5 and data[0] is equal to 93 and data[1] is equal to 0 and data[2] is equal to 0 and data[3] is equal to 128 and data[4] is equal to 0:
        Return "lzma"
    
    Return "none"

Process called "determine_tar_format_from_header" that takes header as TARHeader returns String:
    If header.magic is equal to "ustar ":
        If header.version is equal to "00":
            Return "ustar"
        Otherwise:
            Return "pax"
    Otherwise if header.magic is equal to "ustar\0":
        Return "gnu"
    Otherwise:
        Return "unknown"

Process called "expand_file_list" that takes files as List[String] and config as TARConfig returns List[String]:
    Let expanded_files be list containing
    
    For each file_path in files:
        If is_directory with path as file_path:
            Let directory_files be list_directory_recursively with path as file_path and config as config
            For each dir_file in directory_files:
                Add dir_file to expanded_files
        Otherwise:
            If should_include_file with path as file_path and config as config:
                Add file_path to expanded_files
    
    Return expanded_files

Process called "should_include_file" that takes path as String and config as TARConfig returns Boolean:
    If length of config.exclusion_patterns is greater than 0:
        For each pattern in config.exclusion_patterns:
            If matches_pattern with path as path and pattern as pattern:
                Return false
    
    If length of config.inclusion_patterns is greater than 0:
        For each pattern in config.inclusion_patterns:
            If matches_pattern with path as path and pattern as pattern:
                Return true
        Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "convert_bytes_to_string" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Convert byte array to string using UTF-8 encoding
    Let result be ""
    For each byte_value in bytes:
        Let character be get_character_from_code with code as byte_value
        Set result to result plus character
    Return result

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Process called "slice_byte_array" that takes data as List[Integer] and start as Integer and end as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Extract slice of byte array
    Let result be list containing
    For i from start to (end minus 1):
        If i is less than length of data:
            Add data[i] to result
    Return result

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "check_file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists using system file operations
    Return system_call_file_exists with path as path

Process called "find_missing_files" that takes files as List[String] returns List[String]:
    Let missing be list containing
    For each file_path in files:
        Let exists be check_file_exists with path as file_path
        If not exists:
            Add file_path to missing
    Return missing

Process called "ensure_directory_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Create directory and parent directories if needed using system operations
    Return system_call_create_directory_recursive with path as path

Process called "get_character_from_code" that takes code as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert UTF-8 code point to character using system encoding functions
    Return system_call_utf8_code_to_character with code as code

Note: Low-level TAR implementation functions (Production implementations needed)
