Process called "parse_tar_format_from_string" that takes format as String returns TARFormat:
    Note: Parse TAR format from string
    Match format:
        When "ustar":
            Return USTAR
        When "gnu":
            Return GNU
        When "pax":
            Return PAX
        Otherwise:
            Return USTAR

Process called "parse_compression_from_string" that takes compression as String returns TARCompression:
    Note: Parse compression format from string
    Match compression:
        When "none":
            Return None
        When "gzip":
            Return GZIP
        When "bzip2":
            Return BZIP2
        When "lzma":
            Return LZMA
        When "xz":
            Return XZ
        Otherwise:
            Return None